narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: In this course I learned how to apply a broader concept (the Dionysian) across a variety of material. I was pushed to think critically and dig deep with class readings. Students also had a lot of freedom when it came to class assignments, which was a unique challenge on its own.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: The class materials were very interesting and there was a good balance of academic and artistic in them. One part that I disliked was that the student presentations were supposed to take 15 minutes but usually extended for most of the class, and I would have preferred to hear what the professor could tell us about the topic instead. I also would have liked more of a focus on the comic Dionysian.

The strengths of this course are that the material is very entertaining and the professor is extremely knowledgeable about it. This course was very much how I imagined a small liberal arts seminar: creative, independent, and about a niche topic/works. In terms of improvement, some instructions when it came to assignments/assignment deadlines could have been clearer.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes! It will change the way you see the world.

Yes, I think this is a great class to take. I found it both fun and intellectually challenging, and always looked forward to it even though it was on a Friday afternoon. If you're looking for a unique course and a very discussion-based one, I highly recommend it.

Definitely recommend the course everyone. Professor Symiris is one of the smartest and most inspiring professors I have met at Yale. It was refreshing to have a Mediterrenean professor that I felt close to my culture and to learn from. This course is a must on your way to become a truly well-rounded individual. Professor Symiris always facilitates amazing discussion.
